(It's good.)

775
00:28:31,183 --> 00:28:33,022
(You know how to cook.)

776
00:28:33,023 --> 00:28:34,592
For real?

777
00:28:34,593 --> 00:28:35,993
(Skills that impress people)

778
00:28:36,793 --> 00:28:38,762
(The commonly acknowledged head chef of the Mushroom House)

779
00:28:38,763 --> 00:28:40,932
(Even the rival approves.)

780
00:28:40,933 --> 00:28:44,703
I can catch what kind of food people like...

781
00:28:44,763 --> 00:28:46,603
and cook it well.

782
00:28:48,173 --> 00:28:50,503
I've seen Hyun Wook cook.

783
00:28:51,073 --> 00:28:54,043
From what I see, he's a kindergartner. A baby.

784
00:28:54,773 --> 00:28:57,183
I know for sure that I'll beat him.

785
00:29:09,293 --> 00:29:12,233
The dish I prepared is boiled pork.

786
00:29:14,093 --> 00:29:15,532
With yogurt.

787
00:29:15,533 --> 00:29:18,303
It's easy-to-make boiled pork made with yogurt.

788
00:29:18,833 --> 00:29:21,202
To get rid of the meaty smell,

789
00:29:21,203 --> 00:29:22,902
you need to add ginger and more.

790
00:29:22,903 --> 00:29:24,672
But it's a hassle. By simply pouring in yogurt,

791
00:29:24,673 --> 00:29:26,242
you can make boiled pork that has no meaty smell.

792
00:29:26,243 --> 00:29:27,412
(Removing the meaty smell with just yogurt)

793
00:29:27,413 --> 00:29:28,413
Pork boiled with yogurt.

794
00:29:28,414 --> 00:29:30,343
How you make it is witty too, right?

795
00:29:30,943 --> 00:29:33,483
I'm sure Chef Ahn Sung Jae will be quite surprised.

796
00:29:36,423 --> 00:29:38,953
All that's left is for the meat to cook evenly.

797
00:29:44,323 --> 00:29:45,693
Boiled pork?

798
00:29:47,593 --> 00:29:50,703
It seemed like Kangnam was making boiled pork.

799
00:29:51,763 --> 00:29:54,502
I was wondering what kind of dish I should make...

800
00:29:54,503 --> 00:29:55,873
for the judges.

801
00:29:56,943 --> 00:29:59,713
There were quite a handful of chives left in the fridge.

802
00:29:59,973 --> 00:30:02,343
With that, I thought of making chive pancake.

803
00:30:05,983 --> 00:30:07,353
Cut the chives,

804
00:30:07,813 --> 00:30:09,123
the carrots,

805
00:30:09,353 --> 00:30:10,953
and even Cheongyang chili peppers.

806
00:30:11,723 --> 00:30:13,453
It needs a bit of minced garlic too.

807
00:30:13,953 --> 00:30:16,063
Seasoning is done with fermented tuna sauce.

808
00:30:18,793 --> 00:30:21,392
Lastly, add in a mix of pancake mix...

809
00:30:21,393 --> 00:30:22,633
and frying mix.

810
00:30:23,633 --> 00:30:27,273
They help make the pancake crispier in texture.

811
00:30:29,573 --> 00:30:32,143
Measurements? I'm not a pro at it.

812
00:30:32,413 --> 00:30:33,642
I add as much as I think is needed.

813
00:30:33,643 --> 00:30:35,683
(Potato relies on his feelings to win.)

814
00:30:36,983 --> 00:30:39,782
What makes my dish special is the sauce.

815
00:30:39,783 --> 00:30:43,323
I can't let you in on the recipe. It's confidential.

816
00:30:45,283 --> 00:30:46,593
(Half of an onion)

817
00:30:47,053 --> 00:30:48,753
(1 Cheongyang chili pepper)

818
00:30:49,263 --> 00:30:51,693
(30mL of soy sauce, 20mL of plum extract, 10mL of vinegar)

819
00:30:52,333 --> 00:30:54,363
(10g of chili powder, 5g of sesame seeds)

820
00:30:55,863 --> 00:30:58,603
(Potato's confidential sauce is complete.)

821
00:31:02,603 --> 00:31:06,073
What matters the most in boiled pork is how cooked the meat is.

822
00:31:08,673 --> 00:31:09,813
It's still red.

823
00:31:12,983 --> 00:31:14,482
I have a feeling I'll lose.

824
00:31:14,483 --> 00:31:16,553
(Cutting the other piece of meat)

825
00:31:19,393 --> 00:31:21,622
The meat didn't cook as quickly...

826
00:31:21,623 --> 00:31:23,993
as I imagined, which made me nervous.

827
00:31:32,103 --> 00:31:34,103
I thought there was a possibility I could lose.

828
00:31:37,203 --> 00:31:41,243
(Cooking Master Potato starts cooking chive pancake.)

829
00:31:43,083 --> 00:31:46,783
Honestly, it's my first time making pancake.

830
00:31:52,693 --> 00:31:54,753
It was harder than I imagined.

831
00:31:56,123 --> 00:31:58,023
(Laughing)

832
00:32:00,063 --> 00:32:02,562
(The pancake is turning into a mess.)

833
00:32:02,563 --> 00:32:06,473
Time kept ticking, and I started feeling more nervous.

834
00:32:07,473 --> 00:32:09,303
(Glancing)

835
00:32:14,043 --> 00:32:16,013
(Messy with oil)

836
00:32:18,343 --> 00:32:20,283
This isn't easy. I bet you'll win, Kangnam.

837
00:32:20,383 --> 00:32:23,083
No way. I'm on the brink of failing right now.

838
00:32:26,053 --> 00:32:29,723
(Is "Culinary Class Wars" about to end with despair?)

839
00:32:30,423 --> 00:32:32,792
- I want sicklepod tea.
- Sicklepod tea.

840
00:32:32,793 --> 00:32:34,092
(Tae Ri and Sung Jae are out in the yard.)

841
00:32:34,093 --> 00:32:35,833
I will go with deodeok tea.

842
00:32:37,163 --> 00:32:39,602
I love this place. Do you sit here every evening?

843
00:32:39,603 --> 00:32:42,503
No, we don't have the time to do that every day.

844
00:32:42,803 --> 00:32:43,873
Do you not have the time?

845
00:32:47,173 --> 00:32:48,513
Are things going the way you imagined?

846
00:32:50,413 --> 00:32:51,443
No.

847
00:32:54,683 --> 00:32:55,783
Right now,

848
00:32:57,123 --> 00:32:59,123
I feel pressured and a sense of responsibility.

849
00:32:59,993 --> 00:33:01,123
Pressured about what?

850
00:33:01,393 --> 00:33:05,563
I should help the kids to experience the stage,

851
00:33:05,933 --> 00:33:08,463
but I don't want the experience...

852
00:33:08,663 --> 00:33:10,662
to be too hardcore like a class.

853
00:33:10,663 --> 00:33:14,033
I want them to be able to enjoy it.

854
00:33:14,203 --> 00:33:17,143
But we're pressed for time.

855
00:33:18,043 --> 00:33:19,213
I'm not sure...

856
00:33:20,973 --> 00:33:22,243
But what do the kids want?

857
00:33:24,213 --> 00:33:25,242
The kids?

858
00:33:25,243 --> 00:33:26,483
They...

859
00:33:28,183 --> 00:33:29,282
I'm not asking about what you want.

860
00:33:29,283 --> 00:33:31,222
What kind of performance do they want to put up?

861
00:33:31,223 --> 00:33:33,823
(What kind of performance do they want to put up?)

862
00:33:36,523 --> 00:33:37,823
I never asked.

863
00:33:39,693 --> 00:33:41,163
I should ask them.

864
00:33:41,863 --> 00:33:43,403
I'm not sure, but it's what I think.

865
00:33:43,633 --> 00:33:45,502
To me, communication is the most important.

866
00:33:45,503 --> 00:33:47,072
Communicating with the children.

867
00:33:47,073 --> 00:33:49,702
I have children, but when I meet a child,

868
00:33:49,703 --> 00:33:52,043
I figure out what they want first...

869
00:33:52,443 --> 00:33:55,013
before making something for them.

870
00:33:55,313 --> 00:33:57,643
But it's so hard. How do you do it?

871
00:33:57,783 --> 00:33:59,052
I'm not an expert,

872
00:33:59,053 --> 00:34:01,512
but I read books to learn how we could raise our kids well.

873
00:34:01,513 --> 00:34:04,022
- I've given it a bit of thought.
- Yes.

874
00:34:04,023 --> 00:34:06,622
Instead of categorizing ourselves as a father and a child...

875
00:34:06,623 --> 00:34:08,422
or a teacher and a student,

876
00:34:08,423 --> 00:34:10,923
- we should break the system.
- Okay.

877
00:34:11,193 --> 00:34:13,992
We should meet eye to eye.

878
00:34:13,993 --> 00:34:18,033
I try my best to see things from their perspective.

879
00:34:18,203 --> 00:34:20,933
I think it helps with communicating with them.

880
00:34:22,273 --> 00:34:24,742
(She has another concern.)

881
00:34:24,743 --> 00:34:27,443
I came here as a teacher,

882
00:34:27,873 --> 00:34:31,813
and I have a schedule to follow.

883
00:34:32,183 --> 00:34:36,182
I'm pressured to finish it all before the day of the performance.

884
00:34:36,183 --> 00:34:38,623
There is so much I want to teach them,

885
00:34:38,683 --> 00:34:41,893
but day by day, we make mistakes and get delayed.

886
00:34:43,163 --> 00:34:44,623
We're at a point...

887
00:34:45,323 --> 00:34:46,662
where I need to be firm.

888
00:34:46,663 --> 00:34:48,162
- I have to be strict.
- Are you going to do that?

889
00:34:48,163 --> 00:34:50,263
Yes, we're in such a situation.

890
00:34:50,533 --> 00:34:52,532
You have to make more progress,

891
00:34:52,533 --> 00:34:53,802
but things get disorderly.

892
00:34:53,803 --> 00:34:56,172
Yes. Increasingly more.

893
00:34:56,173 --> 00:34:58,472
(She must lead the children well as the teacher.)

894
00:34:58,473 --> 00:35:00,412
I have to act as their pillar.

895
00:35:00,413 --> 00:35:02,312
(She feels pressured to teach them more.)

896
00:35:02,313 --> 00:35:03,583
I think it's like this.

897
00:35:04,183 --> 00:35:05,753
I'm not a teacher,

898
00:35:06,183 --> 00:35:08,782
but I think there is only so much a teacher can do.

899
00:35:08,783 --> 00:35:10,783
(Sung Jae thinks there is only so much a teacher can do.)

900
00:35:13,253 --> 00:35:14,553
It's up to them.

901
00:35:15,453 --> 00:35:18,263
I'm cool-headed in things like this. It's their responsibility.

902
00:35:18,423 --> 00:35:20,232
There could be kids who take things in twisted ways...

903
00:35:20,233 --> 00:35:22,162
and rival against the teacher...

904
00:35:22,163 --> 00:35:23,832
even if they like acting.

905
00:35:23,833 --> 00:35:25,562
I don't know, but there could be many kinds.

906
00:35:25,563 --> 00:35:26,573
Sure.

907
00:35:26,703 --> 00:35:28,333
"Is that how you're going to be? It's your choice."

908
00:35:28,773 --> 00:35:30,643
"You can sit down..."

909
00:35:30,743 --> 00:35:34,442
"and do this properly, or just forget it."

910
00:35:34,443 --> 00:35:35,782
"It's your choice."

911
00:35:35,783 --> 00:35:37,843
I think kids that age...

912
00:35:38,043 --> 00:35:39,882
are ready to listen to you,

913
00:35:39,883 --> 00:35:41,112
although guidance is necessary.

914
00:35:41,113 --> 00:35:42,982
And for them,

915
00:35:42,983 --> 00:35:46,153
it's an opportunity to make their own decisions.

916
00:35:46,523 --> 00:35:48,393
I think it could be very important.

917
00:35:49,693 --> 00:35:51,593
Personally, as a parent,

918
00:35:52,023 --> 00:35:53,393
I see my kids as my equals.

919
00:35:53,633 --> 00:35:56,502
If I think that they have the ability to make decisions,

920
00:35:56,503 --> 00:35:57,933
I let them use it.

921
00:35:58,063 --> 00:35:59,672
They are also responsible for those decisions.

922
00:35:59,673 --> 00:36:02,943
People might think I'm cruel,

923
00:36:03,103 --> 00:36:04,643
but in this society,

924
00:36:05,073 --> 00:36:08,313
our choices build our next steps.

925
00:36:08,773 --> 00:36:12,342
I believe this helps to prepare them for society.

926
00:36:12,343 --> 00:36:15,152
I want to condense everything I know...

927
00:36:15,153 --> 00:36:17,753
and teach them.

928
00:36:17,923 --> 00:36:19,122
When they're out there,

929
00:36:19,123 --> 00:36:20,522
(He wants them to make mature decisions.)

930
00:36:20,523 --> 00:36:23,823
they'll at least live with those values intact.

931
00:36:24,323 --> 00:36:25,763
I hope I provide such an experience.

932
00:36:26,663 --> 00:36:28,963
Whatever they choose is up to them.

933
00:36:30,633 --> 00:36:31,763
That's what I think.

934
00:36:35,003 --> 00:36:36,003
My gosh.

935
00:36:36,303 --> 00:36:37,702
(Thumbs up)

936
00:36:37,703 --> 00:36:38,743
No, no.

937
00:36:40,143 --> 00:36:41,643
No wonder you're a dad.

938
00:36:41,743 --> 00:36:43,043
But I have a feeling...

939
00:36:44,543 --> 00:36:47,183
you'll do a great job since you gave it so much thought.

940
00:36:48,183 --> 00:36:49,323
- Do you think so?
- Yes.

941
00:36:51,483 --> 00:36:53,623
I'll stay positive and do my best.

942
00:36:54,593 --> 00:36:55,693
Guys...

943
00:36:57,823 --> 00:36:59,593
I wonder how far along the dishes are.

944
00:37:00,263 --> 00:37:03,432
I bet it's a battlefield in the kitchen right now.

945
00:37:03,433 --> 00:37:04,433
The kitchen?

946
00:37:06,903 --> 00:37:08,633
What did they cook? What is this smell?

947
00:37:10,573 --> 00:37:13,343
- Gosh, the smell...
- Can we go in?

948
00:37:14,273 --> 00:37:15,313
Yes.

949
00:37:17,243 --> 00:37:18,243
Welcome.

950
00:37:21,113 --> 00:37:22,113
Welcome.

951
00:37:22,723 --> 00:37:24,223
- They look guilty of something.
- Welcome.

952
00:37:24,923 --> 00:37:26,093
- Yes.
- Welcome.

953
00:37:26,623 --> 00:37:28,052
We cooked with our lives on the line.

954
00:37:28,053 --> 00:37:29,122
(The table looks extraordinary.)

955
00:37:29,123 --> 00:37:30,762
Please be heartless with the critique.

956
00:37:30,763 --> 00:37:31,893
- "Heartless?" - Yes.

957
00:37:32,163 --> 00:37:34,232
All right. Please put on the blindfold.

958
00:37:34,233 --> 00:37:36,563
(Putting on the judge's blindfold)

959
00:37:38,433 --> 00:37:40,603
(Judge Ahn Sung Jae)

960
00:37:41,433 --> 00:37:43,703
(Judge Kim Tae Ri)

961
00:37:44,543 --> 00:37:46,712
I wonder how Chef Ahn will judge it.

962
00:37:46,713 --> 00:37:49,243
(Blindfolded critique begins.)

963
00:37:49,613 --> 00:37:50,983
I really can't see anything.

964
00:37:51,243 --> 00:37:53,512
- No, you can't.
- I can't.

965
00:37:53,513 --> 00:37:54,612
You can't see.

966
00:37:54,613 --> 00:37:56,052
(He's relaxed thanks to his experience.)

967
00:37:56,053 --> 00:37:57,123
I'll open it.

968
00:37:57,953 --> 00:38:01,193
(Revealing the dishes)

969
00:38:02,893 --> 00:38:04,192
The first dish.

970
00:38:04,193 --> 00:38:06,362
We'll serve you the same dish.

971
00:38:06,363 --> 00:38:08,462
(Dish 1: Yogurt Boiled Pork)

972
00:38:08,463 --> 00:38:10,903
The pork can feel too greasy on its own.

973
00:38:11,533 --> 00:38:12,573
It's so greasy.

974
00:38:15,133 --> 00:38:16,743
I prepared...

975
00:38:17,443 --> 00:38:20,312
raw garlic and ripe kimchi to eat with the pork.

976
00:38:20,313 --> 00:38:21,873
(Raw garlic and ripe kimchi)

977
00:38:22,913 --> 00:38:24,483
Everyone loves meat.

978
00:38:25,443 --> 00:38:27,783
I'll most likely win.

979
00:38:29,323 --> 00:38:31,082
(There are no officers to assist with the tasting,)

980
00:38:31,083 --> 00:38:33,793
(so the participants will feed the judges.)

981
00:38:35,993 --> 00:38:37,722
(Matching the amount of ssamjang)

982
00:38:37,723 --> 00:38:39,632
(The chef approves.)

983
00:38:39,633 --> 00:38:40,692
- The 1st dish.
- The 1st dish.

984
00:38:40,693 --> 00:38:42,392
- I'll put it in your mouth.
- Please open your mouth.

985
00:38:42,393 --> 00:38:43,832
- Okay.
- Smell it.

986
00:38:43,833 --> 00:38:45,903
It's right here. Open up your mouth and smell it.

987
00:38:47,573 --> 00:38:51,703
It smells like a ripe radish water kimchi.

988
00:38:52,173 --> 00:38:54,212
(He doesn't know what the dish is or who cooked it.)

989
00:38:54,213 --> 00:38:55,873
- We'll try tasting it.
- Okay.

990
00:38:55,943 --> 00:38:58,042
(Here comes the boiled pork.)

991
00:38:58,043 --> 00:38:59,143
It's a bit big.

992
00:38:59,813 --> 00:39:00,983
Please close your mouth.

993
00:39:04,023 --> 00:39:05,353
It's boiled pork.

994
00:39:12,063 --> 00:39:14,463
He looks exactly like what I saw on television.

995
00:39:14,763 --> 00:39:16,533
- His posture is so scary.
- His posture...

996
00:39:18,033 --> 00:39:19,602
He looks scary from this angle.

997
00:39:19,603 --> 00:39:21,033
(The angle makes them nervous.)

998
00:39:25,243 --> 00:39:27,242
How long did we talk for?

999
00:39:27,243 --> 00:39:28,943
When did you boil this?

1000
00:39:30,283 --> 00:39:31,943
(He can hardly breathe.)

1001
00:39:32,513 --> 00:39:33,513
Raw garlic.

1002
00:39:33,613 --> 00:39:35,853
It wasn't even an hour.

1003
00:39:38,983 --> 00:39:40,123
An hour?

1004
00:39:42,793 --> 00:39:44,863
If I may talk about just the meat,

1005
00:39:45,623 --> 00:39:48,832
it should have been cooked a little more. A bit more.

1006
00:39:48,833 --> 00:39:49,962
(The pork wasn't cooked evenly.)

1007
00:39:49,963 --> 00:39:51,933
When it came into my mouth, I knew it was boiled pork.

1008
00:39:52,433 --> 00:39:54,003
It wasn't cooked properly.

1009
00:39:54,103 --> 00:39:56,403
He must not have had enough time.

1010
00:39:56,843 --> 00:39:59,713
Suddenly, the raw garlic became prominent.

1011
00:39:59,943 --> 00:40:01,643
Its kick stung me.

1012
00:40:03,013 --> 00:40:06,553
I wondered if he had tasted it before serving me.

1013
00:40:07,583 --> 00:40:09,523
I think...

1014
00:40:10,083 --> 00:40:12,852
you could have balanced the tastes more before feeding us.

1015
00:40:12,853 --> 00:40:14,293
But I get the picture...

1016
00:40:15,293 --> 00:40:17,623
of the overall taste.

1017
00:40:18,823 --> 00:40:21,993
Chef Ahn is sharp.

1018
00:40:22,433 --> 00:40:23,503
I'm scared of him.

1019
00:40:26,373 --> 00:40:29,643
I actually liked it. It goes well with ssamjang.

1020
00:40:29,803 --> 00:40:31,402
The fatty part was chewy.

1021
00:40:31,403 --> 00:40:34,013
It had a nice texture.

1022
00:40:34,473 --> 00:40:36,843
I knew I could rely on her. She has good taste.

1023
00:40:39,553 --> 00:40:42,252
(Washing their mouths before the next tasting)

1024
00:40:42,253 --> 00:40:44,223
- Now, the 2nd dish.
- The 2nd dish.

1025
00:40:44,823 --> 00:40:46,592
(Dish 2: Chive Pancake)

1026
00:40:46,593 --> 00:40:49,352
I have a sense of responsibility for my cooking.

1027
00:40:49,353 --> 00:40:51,093
I care about how polished it is.

1028
00:40:51,423 --> 00:40:52,563
I'd better rip this part.

1029
00:40:54,033 --> 00:40:55,633
I'm confident about my chive pancake.

1030
00:40:56,133 --> 00:40:57,203
Kangnam,

1031
00:40:57,603 --> 00:40:59,573
you'd better brace yourself.

1032
00:41:00,703 --> 00:41:02,942
- Now, the 2nd dish.
- The 2nd dish.

1033
00:41:02,943 --> 00:41:05,243
We'll prepare the same amount of the same dish.

1034
00:41:05,643 --> 00:41:06,873
We'll feed you right away.

1035
00:41:08,943 --> 00:41:10,142
Try smelling it.

1036
00:41:10,143 --> 00:41:11,713
(Again, they get to smell it first.)

1037
00:41:14,113 --> 00:41:15,252
It smells sweet.

1038
00:41:15,253 --> 00:41:17,623
(Here comes the chive pancake.)

1039
00:41:18,023 --> 00:41:19,892
All the way.

1040
00:41:19,893 --> 00:41:23,263
(Crunchy)

1041
00:41:24,393 --> 00:41:27,133
(Super nervous)

1042
00:41:27,963 --> 00:41:31,662
(Tasting)

1043
00:41:31,663 --> 00:41:32,733
It's a pancake.

1044
00:41:34,003 --> 00:41:35,003
Yes.

1045
00:41:35,533 --> 00:41:36,773
What kind of pancake is it?

1046
00:41:42,813 --> 00:41:44,742
You gave me an edge piece.

1047
00:41:44,743 --> 00:41:45,743
Yes.

1048
00:41:46,583 --> 00:41:48,553
- Yes, the edge.
- It's...

1049
00:41:48,983 --> 00:41:50,083
It's...

1050
00:41:51,953 --> 00:41:54,853
Whether it was green onions or chives,

1051
00:41:56,193 --> 00:41:59,023
it was overcooked. It tastes bitter because of it.

1052
00:42:00,633 --> 00:42:01,693
Whatever this is.

1053
00:42:02,033 --> 00:42:04,403
(Rummaging)

1054
00:42:05,263 --> 00:42:08,073
When I took a bite, I thought it was a cookie.

1055
00:42:08,303 --> 00:42:10,203
But not all crunchy textures are good.

1056
00:42:10,403 --> 00:42:12,843
When it's too crunchy, it means it's dehydrated.

1057
00:42:13,073 --> 00:42:16,783
It means the ingredients have started to burn.

1058
00:42:16,983 --> 00:42:18,313
When I chewed on it,

1059
00:42:18,913 --> 00:42:20,452
it tasted burnt at the end.

1060
00:42:20,453 --> 00:42:21,583
But, okay.

1061
00:42:22,213 --> 00:42:24,483
It's possible if it's the edge of a pancake.

1062
00:42:24,923 --> 00:42:26,322
- Can I try another bite?
- Sure.

1063
00:42:26,323 --> 00:42:27,452
But a middle piece.

1064
00:42:27,453 --> 00:42:30,792
This one is like a cookie.

1065
00:42:30,793 --> 00:42:32,862
- Okay, a middle piece.
- From the middle.

1066
00:42:32,863 --> 00:42:35,933
(A 2nd tasting session with a middle piece)

1067
00:42:36,233 --> 00:42:37,263
Okay.

1068
00:42:43,173 --> 00:42:45,042
(I see.)

1069
00:42:45,043 --> 00:42:46,043
That was a middle piece.

1070
00:42:46,044 --> 00:42:48,143
It's still crunchy.

1071
00:42:49,943 --> 00:42:52,853
(Potato Teacher feels thirsty.)

1072
00:42:52,983 --> 00:42:54,883
The first piece tasted burnt,

1073
00:42:54,983 --> 00:42:55,983
and the second piece...

1074
00:42:57,383 --> 00:42:59,623
tasted familiar.

1075
00:43:01,023 --> 00:43:02,453
I prayed...

1076
00:43:02,523 --> 00:43:05,423
that the second piece tasted good.

1077
00:43:06,933 --> 00:43:10,002
Please tell us if you like the first dish...

1078
00:43:10,003 --> 00:43:11,302
or the second dish.

1079
00:43:11,303 --> 00:43:12,332
Just a minute.

1080
00:43:12,333 --> 00:43:13,972
- Me too. I need to think.
- Let me think.

1081
00:43:13,973 --> 00:43:16,033
I'm very nervous.

1082
00:43:19,443 --> 00:43:22,773
- It's about taste and texture, yes?
- Yes.

1083
00:43:22,883 --> 00:43:24,182
- Taste and texture.
- Taste and texture.

1084
00:43:24,183 --> 00:43:25,212
Also, its overall quality.

1085
00:43:25,213 --> 00:43:27,052
- Yes.
- You can be heartless.

1086
00:43:27,053 --> 00:43:28,083
(Also, overall quality)

1087
00:43:30,353 --> 00:43:31,483
You look torn.

1088
00:43:31,583 --> 00:43:33,622
- It's hard.
- It's harder than you think.

1089
00:43:33,623 --> 00:43:35,052
- Is it hard?
- It's hard.

1090
00:43:35,053 --> 00:43:36,152
- It's hard.
- Really?

1091
00:43:36,153 --> 00:43:37,163
- Yes.
- Yes.

1092
00:43:37,863 --> 00:43:42,163
Honestly, I can't say much about the overall quality.

1093
00:43:42,663 --> 00:43:44,003
I'll go with my personal taste.

1094
00:43:46,833 --> 00:43:48,072
- I'm ready.
- Have you decided?

1095
00:43:48,073 --> 00:43:49,133
- Yes.
- Okay.

1096
00:43:50,043 --> 00:43:54,373
Now, vote with your fingers.

1097
00:43:55,813 --> 00:43:57,612
One, two, three.

1098
00:43:57,613 --> 00:43:58,411
(What will the judges choose?)

1099
00:43:59,935 --> 00:44:04,335
Now, vote with your fingers.

1100
00:44:05,735 --> 00:44:07,404
One, two, three.

1101
00:44:07,405 --> 00:44:08,405
(What will the judges choose?)

1102
00:44:09,605 --> 00:44:12,775
(2: Chive Pancake, 1: Boiled Pork)

1103
00:44:13,585 --> 00:44:16,285
(Tae Ri picked Kangnam's boiled pork.)

1104
00:44:16,785 --> 00:44:19,855
(Sung Jae picked Cooking Master Potato's chive pancake.)

1105
00:44:20,155 --> 00:44:22,884
All right. Okay.

1106
00:44:22,885 --> 00:44:24,224
You can put your arms down.

1107
00:44:24,225 --> 00:44:26,254
You can take off your blindfolds...

1108
00:44:26,255 --> 00:44:28,495
and check who made what.

1109
00:44:28,995 --> 00:44:30,834
You tied it really tight, didn't you?

1110
00:44:30,835 --> 00:44:33,735
There is the blindfold mark on your nose.

1111
00:44:33,835 --> 00:44:35,064
Was that necessary?

1112
00:44:35,065 --> 00:44:36,774
- You too.
- Tae Ri too. Why so tight?

1113
00:44:36,775 --> 00:44:38,934
- I think it's the only way.
- Yes.

1114
00:44:38,935 --> 00:44:40,605
I did it for fairness.

1115
00:44:40,945 --> 00:44:43,714
I picked the pancake. What about you?

1116
00:44:43,715 --> 00:44:44,715
- The pork.
- Pork.

1117
00:44:44,716 --> 00:44:46,044
- Yes.
- Exactly.

1118
00:44:46,045 --> 00:44:48,685
Can we ask you for the reason?

1119
00:44:48,885 --> 00:44:50,584
I just like boiled pork.

1120
00:44:50,585 --> 00:44:51,615
You like it.

1121
00:44:52,355 --> 00:44:55,425
Well, the boiled pork was good to me too.

1122
00:44:56,895 --> 00:44:58,054
(They're getting the chills.)

1123
00:44:58,055 --> 00:45:00,465
But if the standards are high,

1124
00:45:00,865 --> 00:45:02,665
it isn't high in quality.

1125
00:45:03,435 --> 00:45:05,595
- Yes. It could be better.
- Not high in quality.

1126
00:45:06,135 --> 00:45:08,435
That was what disappointed me.

1127
00:45:08,535 --> 00:45:10,875
Too bad. It's too bad.

1128
00:45:11,135 --> 00:45:13,075
I want to try again.

1129
00:45:13,305 --> 00:45:16,374
At first, I thought it was burnt...

1130
00:45:16,375 --> 00:45:17,774
or overcooked.

1131
00:45:17,775 --> 00:45:19,244
Yes. There was a burnt aftertaste.

1132
00:45:19,245 --> 00:45:20,245
- Really?
- Yes.

1133
00:45:20,246 --> 00:45:21,984
The middle part was okay.

1134
00:45:21,985 --> 00:45:23,485
When I had it with the onion,

1135
00:45:23,585 --> 00:45:27,125
it tasted pleasant together.

1136
00:45:27,455 --> 00:45:31,125
Then I asked myself what was worse.

1137
00:45:31,325 --> 00:45:34,095
A burnt pancake or an undercooked pork?

1138
00:45:34,395 --> 00:45:38,294
I wondered what might be more important.

1139
00:45:38,295 --> 00:45:41,404
In the end, I thought the pancake...

1140
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:44,405
had better overall quality.

1141
00:45:45,275 --> 00:45:46,545
Okay.

1142
00:45:46,645 --> 00:45:47,875
I see.

1143
00:45:47,975 --> 00:45:50,974
We tied, but I was happier...

1144
00:45:50,975 --> 00:45:52,245
to get Chef Ahn's vote.

1145
00:45:52,815 --> 00:45:56,114
I took it as receiving...

1146
00:45:56,115 --> 00:45:58,485
his acknowledgement.

1147
00:46:00,325 --> 00:46:02,954
I think I'll be able to cook it well next time.

1148
00:46:02,955 --> 00:46:04,595
(His attempt to become a Cooking Master continues.)

1149
00:46:04,855 --> 00:46:06,154
Anyway, we both worked hard.

1150
00:46:06,155 --> 00:46:07,664
- But I'm glad.
- Sure.

1151
00:46:07,665 --> 00:46:10,334
We almost had a falling out, but we tied.

1152
00:46:10,335 --> 00:46:11,794
- Good work.
- Good work.

1153
00:46:11,795 --> 00:46:12,864
Let's go ahead and eat.

1154
00:46:12,865 --> 00:46:14,064
- Yes.
- Okay.

1155
00:46:14,065 --> 00:46:16,105
(It's finally time for dinner.)

1156
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:18,275
(A special menu by Cooking Master Potato)

1157
00:46:18,276 --> 00:46:20,175
Here is the ramyeon.

1158
00:46:20,575 --> 00:46:21,575
- That looks good.
- Enjoy.

1159
00:46:21,576 --> 00:46:23,775
- Please go ahead.
- I'll enjoy it.

1160
00:46:23,875 --> 00:46:26,275
Thank you for the food.

1161
00:46:27,315 --> 00:46:29,285
(Slurping)

1162
00:46:30,415 --> 00:46:31,855
(Slurping)

1163
00:46:33,385 --> 00:46:36,725
(He's diving into the bowl.)

1164
00:46:37,655 --> 00:46:39,095
- It's so good.
- Isn't it?

1165
00:46:40,195 --> 00:46:41,494
It goes perfectly with pepper.

1166
00:46:41,495 --> 00:46:43,634
- I added a lot of pepper.
- He added pepper.

1167
00:46:43,635 --> 00:46:45,895
Why did you add pepper? I saw you adding it.

1168
00:46:46,535 --> 00:46:47,535
Did you think it needed some?

1169
00:46:47,536 --> 00:46:50,234
Yes. You can smell the pepper when you add it...

1170
00:46:50,235 --> 00:46:51,334
It doesn't smell like pepper, does it?

1171
00:46:51,335 --> 00:46:52,534
He was really scary just now.

1172
00:46:52,535 --> 00:46:54,145
- I know. It was like scolding.
- Pepper...

1173
00:46:54,905 --> 00:46:56,044
Why did you put it in?

1174
00:46:56,045 --> 00:46:57,114
(He's being judged again.)

1175
00:46:57,115 --> 00:46:59,644
I think he has clear ideas of what he wants.

1176
00:46:59,645 --> 00:47:01,084
I'm curious to know what it is.

1177
00:47:01,085 --> 00:47:03,015
I think his personality shows in his cooking.

1178
00:47:03,885 --> 00:47:04,914
Don't you agree?

1179
00:47:04,915 --> 00:47:06,014
That applies to everyone.

1180
00:47:06,015 --> 00:47:07,025
Right?

1181
00:47:07,055 --> 00:47:09,995
When I asked him to cook the tenderloin earlier,

1182
00:47:10,925 --> 00:47:13,124
I questioned whether he could do it.

1183
00:47:13,125 --> 00:47:14,395
But there was no time.

1184
00:47:15,625 --> 00:47:18,135
(His worries were rendered unnecessary.)

1185
00:47:18,935 --> 00:47:21,034
(Hyun Wook barbecued perfectly.)

1186
00:47:21,035 --> 00:47:25,534
When he cooked them, I could see how scary he was.

1187
00:47:25,535 --> 00:47:26,874
I learned that you were a tenacious person.

1188
00:47:26,875 --> 00:47:28,105
- Really?
- No way.

1189
00:47:28,205 --> 00:47:30,345
He can be when it comes to something he wants.

1190
00:47:30,445 --> 00:47:32,815
- I'm scared. He's scary.
- Really?

1191
00:47:33,585 --> 00:47:36,114
- He's scary when he acts.
- Really?

1192
00:47:36,115 --> 00:47:37,785
(This passionate potato can be persistent and tenacious.)

1193
00:47:38,155 --> 00:47:39,685
Today was hectic, wasn't it?

1194
00:47:40,055 --> 00:47:41,085
- Today?
- Yes.

1195
00:47:41,755 --> 00:47:44,094
But I had a lot of fun.

1196
00:47:44,095 --> 00:47:46,965
Anyway, I had a clear goal.

1197
00:47:47,265 --> 00:47:48,495
It was for the kids.

1198
00:47:48,995 --> 00:47:51,395
I like kids,

1199
00:47:51,865 --> 00:47:56,265
and it makes me feel proud to do something for them.

1200
00:47:56,705 --> 00:47:58,435
It allowed me to meet you all too.

1201
00:47:58,675 --> 00:48:00,174
I had a wonderful time.

1202
00:48:00,175 --> 00:48:02,045
(He had a meaningful time.)

1203
00:48:04,145 --> 00:48:07,685
Actually, the day went differently from what I predicted.

1204
00:48:08,915 --> 00:48:10,754
Kids are so innocent.

1205
00:48:10,755 --> 00:48:14,854
They're the most beautiful beings on Earth.

1206
00:48:14,855 --> 00:48:15,855
I was reminded of that.

1207
00:48:17,655 --> 00:48:20,865
I wish for them to remember me for a long time...

1208
00:48:21,265 --> 00:48:22,995
as a fellow teacher...

1209
00:48:23,265 --> 00:48:25,865
whom they spent a fun time with...

1210
00:48:26,535 --> 00:48:30,105
instead of a chef on television.

1211
00:48:30,475 --> 00:48:32,675
I will also cherish...

1212
00:48:32,935 --> 00:48:36,715
their faces, expressions, and our conversations...

1213
00:48:36,945 --> 00:48:38,674
for a long time.

1214
00:48:38,675 --> 00:48:40,085
(He will cherish today for a long time.)

1215
00:48:40,285 --> 00:48:43,214
Please remember the students of Yongheung Elementary School.

1216
00:48:43,215 --> 00:48:45,014
I will. I'll root for you guys.

1217
00:48:45,015 --> 00:48:46,555
Thank you so much for coming today.

1218
00:48:46,655 --> 00:48:47,655
Take care.

1219
00:48:47,656 --> 00:48:49,524
- Bye.
- Bye!

1220
00:48:49,525 --> 00:48:50,595
(Whale Teacher is leaving.)

1221
00:48:51,025 --> 00:48:53,864
- It's chilly.
- Yes, it's chilly.

1222
00:48:53,865 --> 00:48:55,624
The moon is so beautiful today. Look.

1223
00:48:55,625 --> 00:48:57,235
- You're right.
- It's bright.

1224
00:48:57,465 --> 00:48:58,994
- Is it a full moon?
- I don't think so.

1225
00:48:58,995 --> 00:49:00,204
It's almost a full moon.

1226
00:49:00,205 --> 00:49:01,435
Yes. It's really bright.

1227
00:49:03,135 --> 00:49:06,304
Another stormy day has passed.

1228
00:49:06,305 --> 00:49:07,745
(Another stormy day has passed.)

1229
00:49:09,775 --> 00:49:11,474
Classes are starting tomorrow.

1230
00:49:11,475 --> 00:49:12,744
(The acting classes are coming up.)

1231
00:49:12,745 --> 00:49:15,614
I feel like my mind is a clean slate now.

1232
00:49:15,615 --> 00:49:17,214
That is the feeling I have.

1233
00:49:17,215 --> 00:49:20,354
It has been a while, but I feel positive.

1234
00:49:20,355 --> 00:49:23,795
I feel cheered up.

1235
00:49:24,155 --> 00:49:25,595
I'm going to stay focused...

1236
00:49:25,795 --> 00:49:27,964
and clench my teeth.

1237
00:49:27,965 --> 00:49:28,965
(She's determined once again.)

1238
00:49:30,135 --> 00:49:32,795
(A few days later)

1239
00:49:37,275 --> 00:49:40,545
(I'm too exhausted.)

1240
00:49:41,475 --> 00:49:44,275
(I'm exhausted.)

1241
00:49:44,675 --> 00:49:46,374
My heart is feeble.

1242
00:49:46,375 --> 00:49:50,155
(What happened to Ms. Kim?)

1243
00:49:51,755 --> 00:49:53,214
(After Whale Teacher left)

1244
00:49:53,215 --> 00:49:55,255
We really need to discuss this.

1245
00:49:55,985 --> 00:49:57,094
It's our sixth class.

1246
00:49:57,095 --> 00:49:59,294
There is not much time left.

1247
00:49:59,295 --> 00:50:02,125
The run-through is on Friday.

1248
00:50:02,695 --> 00:50:04,835
It's about time we talk about this.

1249
00:50:05,695 --> 00:50:08,365
We're really out of time now.

1250
00:50:08,465 --> 00:50:10,375
We have to put up a performance.

1251
00:50:10,805 --> 00:50:14,375
We'd better practice the scenes in bits.

1252
00:50:14,475 --> 00:50:17,845
I think we need to work on that.

1253
00:50:19,315 --> 00:50:22,785
(After-school acting class's "The Wizard of Oz")

1254
00:50:23,385 --> 00:50:25,915
(Ms. Kim has rewritten it into a total of 7 scenes.)

1255
00:50:26,015 --> 00:50:27,324
(1: Dorothy's Scene)

1256
00:50:27,325 --> 00:50:28,654
(2: Scarecrow's Scene)

1257
00:50:28,655 --> 00:50:30,054
(3: Tin Man's Scene)

1258
00:50:30,055 --> 00:50:31,324
(4: Lion's Scene)

1259
00:50:31,325 --> 00:50:32,794
(5: Witch's Scene)

1260
00:50:32,795 --> 00:50:34,224
(6: Chorus Scene)

1261
00:50:34,225 --> 00:50:36,264
(7: Wizard's Scene)

1262
00:50:36,265 --> 00:50:39,834
Dorothy and Toto, who have fallen...

1263
00:50:39,835 --> 00:50:41,334
on the strange land of Oz,

1264
00:50:41,335 --> 00:50:43,305
go off to find the wizard so they could return home.

1265
00:50:43,875 --> 00:50:46,035
On their journey, they meet Scarecrow,

1266
00:50:46,635 --> 00:50:48,075
the Tin Man,

1267
00:50:48,545 --> 00:50:51,145
and the Cowardly Lion, and they become friends.

1268
00:50:51,745 --> 00:50:54,315
But the Wicked Witch of the West puts them in danger.

1269
00:50:54,785 --> 00:50:57,414
The friends work together to beat the witch,

1270
00:50:57,415 --> 00:50:58,885
and they will sing.

1271
00:50:59,355 --> 00:51:02,854
Finally, they will make their wishes when they meet the Wizard of Oz...

1272
00:51:02,855 --> 00:51:04,195
and the play will come to a close.

1273
00:51:05,425 --> 00:51:07,865
It's my first time directing,

1274
00:51:08,265 --> 00:51:10,065
so I'll have to face it head on.

1275
00:51:11,035 --> 00:51:14,605
Instead of omitting it, can we condense it?

1276
00:51:14,705 --> 00:51:16,734
Yes, I can do that.

1277
00:51:16,735 --> 00:51:18,975
(Tae Ri decided to be bold with reducing the lines.)

1278
00:51:19,105 --> 00:51:20,705
Before we teach them the line of movement,

1279
00:51:20,805 --> 00:51:24,374
we should practice it amongst ourselves.

1280
00:51:24,375 --> 00:51:26,574
Yes, we should practice it from the beginning.

1281
00:51:26,575 --> 00:51:27,644
We have to practice the play.

1282
00:51:27,645 --> 00:51:29,644
Even if Dorothy is walking slowly,

1283
00:51:29,645 --> 00:51:32,154
Toto should go back and forth like this.

1284
00:51:32,155 --> 00:51:33,784
- Sure, we need that.
- Toto should go and see.

1285
00:51:33,785 --> 00:51:35,324
He should keep doing that.

1286
00:51:35,325 --> 00:51:36,655
"I'll let you down..."

1287
00:51:37,295 --> 00:51:38,555
should be said at this point.

1288
00:51:38,655 --> 00:51:39,954
After he says "You are the best!" to the audience,

1289
00:51:39,955 --> 00:51:42,224
- Toto should leave last.
- Sounds good.

1290
00:51:42,225 --> 00:51:44,035
Please play the grand and upbeat music, Kangnam.

1291
00:51:45,835 --> 00:51:48,565
(Kangnam lifts the mood.)

1292
00:51:49,465 --> 00:51:50,474
I can't see.

1293
00:51:50,475 --> 00:51:51,634
(Cheerful)

1294
00:51:51,635 --> 00:51:52,674
