It's a complete mess.

1548
01:01:41,695 --> 01:01:43,394
You can't make the kids memorize it...

1549
01:01:43,395 --> 01:01:44,395
when you can't.

1550
01:01:44,396 --> 01:01:46,734
- Didn't it go like this?
- Yes.

1551
01:01:46,735 --> 01:01:48,304
What was the move for the spreading broadly part?

1552
01:01:48,305 --> 01:01:49,405
Help me this time.

1553
01:01:49,965 --> 01:01:51,334
(The students, the teacher)

1554
01:01:51,335 --> 01:01:52,734
(The teachers, the student)

1555
01:01:52,735 --> 01:01:54,345
- Why are we doing this?
- The roles have changed.

1556
01:01:54,605 --> 01:01:56,205
You were the one who made the moves.

1557
01:01:56,445 --> 01:01:57,514
- What are you doing?
- It's your choreography.

1558
01:01:57,515 --> 01:01:59,614
You said, "Why don't we do it like this?"

1559
01:01:59,615 --> 01:02:00,984
- You're the teacher.
- Even you can't memorize it.

1560
01:02:00,985 --> 01:02:02,614
You have to be on top of everything.

1561
01:02:02,615 --> 01:02:03,785
(Potato Teacher's class is in danger of closing.)

1562
01:02:05,755 --> 01:02:09,425
I wonder if there are too many moves for each part of the lyrics.

1563
01:02:12,295 --> 01:02:15,165
(After the Potato Teacher's class,)

1564
01:02:17,765 --> 01:02:21,465
(he prepares an apple as if he's under a spell.)

1565
01:02:22,065 --> 01:02:23,235
What are you doing?

1566
01:02:27,175 --> 01:02:28,745
You really love apples.

1567
01:02:29,275 --> 01:02:31,375
- The kids gave them to me.
- Right.

1568
01:02:32,875 --> 01:02:34,084
Can I have a bite?

1569
01:02:34,085 --> 01:02:35,245
(Taking a bite right away)

1570
01:02:37,485 --> 01:02:39,454
(He takes a bite too.)

1571
01:02:39,455 --> 01:02:40,954
- It's tasty, isn't it?
- Yes.

1572
01:02:40,955 --> 01:02:42,054
It's so good.

1573
01:02:42,055 --> 01:02:44,955
(The loving brothers share an apple.)

1574
01:02:46,495 --> 01:02:48,665
(Loving it)

1575
01:02:50,065 --> 01:02:52,595
(Hurriedly)

1576
01:02:54,065 --> 01:02:57,875
(It's the only ray of hope in his life in Mungyeong.)

1577
01:02:59,805 --> 01:03:03,605
(The apple-eating time will be continued next time.)

1578
01:03:04,005 --> 01:03:05,174
- What is this?
- Here.

1579
01:03:05,175 --> 01:03:07,114
(Their last task is to read the question notes.)

1580
01:03:07,115 --> 01:03:08,945
Whose note are you the most curious about?

1581
01:03:09,285 --> 01:03:11,115
- I pick...
- The one I'm most curious about?

1582
01:03:11,615 --> 01:03:13,715
- Won Jin.
- Won Jin.

1583
01:03:14,455 --> 01:03:16,385
Won Jin writes very diligently.

1584
01:03:17,455 --> 01:03:19,254
"Ms. Kim, I was really surprised when I heard..."

1585
01:03:19,255 --> 01:03:21,094
"that we were having an outdoor class."

1586
01:03:21,095 --> 01:03:23,865
"North Pole Teacher shocked me too. It was fun today."

1587
01:03:24,135 --> 01:03:26,534
"I don't have questions. I'll do my best."

1588
01:03:26,535 --> 01:03:28,064
"I might not be able to record a video every time."

1589
01:03:28,065 --> 01:03:29,604
"But I'm doing my best."

1590
01:03:29,605 --> 01:03:31,835
"I think I'll record some videos from time to time."

1591
01:03:32,035 --> 01:03:34,174
"Thank you for the class."

1592
01:03:34,175 --> 01:03:35,275
He's cute.

1593
01:03:35,475 --> 01:03:36,844
He is very clever.

1594
01:03:36,845 --> 01:03:38,215
He has good handwriting.

1595
01:03:38,415 --> 01:03:40,515
"I was surprised because Mr. CO came today."

1596
01:03:40,615 --> 01:03:41,845
"And it was fun."

1597
01:03:41,985 --> 01:03:43,845
"I was shocked. It was exciting and fun."

1598
01:03:44,655 --> 01:03:46,885
- It's...
- He got lazy in the end.

1599
01:03:48,155 --> 01:03:49,825
- His formality has disappeared.
- I mean...

1600
01:03:51,725 --> 01:03:52,854
In the end...

1601
01:03:52,855 --> 01:03:54,864
- He's not writing to me anymore.
- No.

1602
01:03:54,865 --> 01:03:56,025
(A clear difference in enthusiasm)

1603
01:03:56,325 --> 01:03:57,994
- Let's read Ha Yun's.
- Who's next?

1604
01:03:57,995 --> 01:03:59,034
Ha Yun is so cute.

1605
01:03:59,035 --> 01:04:00,135
(Next is Ha Yun.)

1606
01:04:01,665 --> 01:04:03,304
He didn't write on the second day.

1607
01:04:03,305 --> 01:04:05,705
"Ms. Kim, why did you climb onto the statue in college?"

1608
01:04:06,605 --> 01:04:08,905
- What? Statue?
- Statue.

1609
01:04:09,005 --> 01:04:10,504
Was it back in your college years?

1610
01:04:10,505 --> 01:04:11,674
It was.

1611
01:04:11,675 --> 01:04:14,514
There's a photo that looks like it's from the 1970s or 1980s.

1612
01:04:14,515 --> 01:04:16,914
- It looks blurry.
- Really?

1613
01:04:16,915 --> 01:04:18,785
- Yes.
- Really?

1614
01:04:20,985 --> 01:04:22,154
- Is it over?
- Is that all?

1615
01:04:22,155 --> 01:04:23,185
Come on.

1616
01:04:24,525 --> 01:04:27,225
(Next question note is...)

1617
01:04:29,195 --> 01:04:30,295
Oh dear.

1618
01:04:31,165 --> 01:04:33,395
- It hurts, doesn't it?
- It's Kyung Mo.

1619
01:04:33,695 --> 01:04:34,935
"When does this end?"

1620
01:04:36,898 --> 01:04:39,668
(Next question note is...)

1621
01:04:41,871 --> 01:04:42,971
Oh dear.

1622
01:04:43,594 --> 01:04:45,864
- It hurts, doesn't it?
- It's Kyung Mo.

1623
01:04:46,264 --> 01:04:47,434
"When does this end?"

1624
01:04:48,804 --> 01:04:50,003
I want to find out too.

1625
01:04:50,004 --> 01:04:51,803
(When does this end?)

1626
01:04:51,804 --> 01:04:54,874
He was thinking such things while smiling all the time.

1627
01:04:56,574 --> 01:04:58,714
(What Kyung Mo truly feels?)

1628
01:04:59,614 --> 01:05:04,114
(When does this end?)

1629
01:05:04,314 --> 01:05:05,584
"When does this end?"

1630
01:05:06,184 --> 01:05:07,624
It's shocking. "When does this end?"

1631
01:05:08,354 --> 01:05:09,553
"When does this end?"

1632
01:05:09,554 --> 01:05:11,253
- It's shocking.
- It's because he's young.

1633
01:05:11,254 --> 01:05:12,924
It's sad to hear that.

1634
01:05:13,324 --> 01:05:14,694
Kyung Mo's still very young.

1635
01:05:16,794 --> 01:05:20,064
(Tae Ri answers the remaining questions.)

1636
01:05:21,304 --> 01:05:23,233
(Ju Eun's question)

1637
01:05:23,234 --> 01:05:27,004
(How can I memorize long lines?)

1638
01:05:28,504 --> 01:05:30,003
(What a great question, Ju Eun!)

1639
01:05:30,004 --> 01:05:31,413
(In my opinion,)

1640
01:05:31,414 --> 01:05:32,843
(instead of memorizing each word,)

1641
01:05:32,844 --> 01:05:34,313
(it'll be better to think about the situation.)

1642
01:05:34,314 --> 01:05:36,513
(Then try to explain the situation to the audience!)

1643
01:05:36,514 --> 01:05:39,213
(If that's a bit hard, you can underline the key words,)

1644
01:05:39,214 --> 01:05:41,624
(and draw a map of your own.)

1645
01:05:43,754 --> 01:05:48,064
(Wrapping up the day while thinking about the kids)

1646
01:05:50,664 --> 01:05:52,863
(Ms. Kim...)

1647
01:05:52,864 --> 01:05:55,604
(and North Pole Teacher go to bed.)

1648
01:05:57,464 --> 01:05:59,634
(What about Potato Teacher, then?)

1649
01:06:04,614 --> 01:06:07,244
(He's staying by himself.)

1650
01:06:08,684 --> 01:06:13,154
(Practicing the rest of the song)

1651
01:06:16,484 --> 01:06:18,693
(Repeating it until he knows it by heart)

1652
01:06:18,694 --> 01:06:21,494
(Repeating it again)

1653
01:06:23,524 --> 01:06:27,664
(The practice for the chorus never ends.)

1654
01:06:29,464 --> 01:06:34,234
(Potato Teacher sang until dawn.)

1655
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:41,414
(Next morning)

1656
01:06:47,484 --> 01:06:51,454
(Potato Teacher is busy with something.)

1657
01:06:53,754 --> 01:06:57,964
(Is he cooking alone in the morning?)

1658
01:06:58,394 --> 01:07:00,394
Make breakfast for everyone.

1659
01:07:01,204 --> 01:07:03,264
- Good.
- Cook breakfast for each.

1660
01:07:04,034 --> 01:07:05,034
Okay.

1661
01:07:05,804 --> 01:07:06,833
Okay.

1662
01:07:06,834 --> 01:07:07,903
(Potato is the 1st player.)

1663
01:07:07,904 --> 01:07:09,004
The closest one to the edge wins.

1664
01:07:09,974 --> 01:07:11,574
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

1665
01:07:12,374 --> 01:07:13,673
- Why?
- It's over.

1666
01:07:13,674 --> 01:07:14,814
It's over, indeed.

1667
01:07:16,544 --> 01:07:19,114
- Fried eggs and...
- Fried eggs.

1668
01:07:19,454 --> 01:07:21,324
- bread, and cheese.
- Cheese and bread.

1669
01:07:21,624 --> 01:07:23,783
- Grill the ham separately.
- That's right.

1670
01:07:23,784 --> 01:07:25,824
Do we have ketchup? Add some ketchup.

1671
01:07:26,294 --> 01:07:27,624
As for the eggs,

1672
01:07:28,464 --> 01:07:30,263
what is it called? Sunshine?

1673
01:07:30,264 --> 01:07:31,634
- Sunny...
- Sunny...

1674
01:07:32,894 --> 01:07:34,504
Something like the sunrise.

1675
01:07:35,164 --> 01:07:37,364
Am I right?

1676
01:07:38,974 --> 01:07:43,204
(He gets help from YouTube again today.)

1677
01:07:44,844 --> 01:07:49,314
(Starting with the toasts)

1678
01:07:50,744 --> 01:07:53,184
(Placing it gently)

1679
01:07:56,654 --> 01:07:58,894
(Throwing around)

1680
01:08:00,354 --> 01:08:03,494
(He shows what he's got early in the morning.)

1681
01:08:05,164 --> 01:08:08,204
(Grinning)

1682
01:08:10,064 --> 01:08:12,273
("It's okay. You grow up pretty only if you have scars.")

1683
01:08:12,274 --> 01:08:14,304
(Mr. CO in Episode 5)

1684
01:08:16,374 --> 01:08:18,914
(Adding lots of filling as ordered)

1685
01:08:20,574 --> 01:08:23,144
(The toasts are somehow ready.)

1686
01:08:24,714 --> 01:08:28,584
(Next is something like the sunrise.)

1687
01:08:30,354 --> 01:08:33,454
(Carefully)

1688
01:08:36,294 --> 01:08:37,364
Darn.

1689
01:08:40,164 --> 01:08:43,734
(It's torn before he grabbed it.)

1690
01:08:45,174 --> 01:08:46,934
(Laughing)

1691
01:08:48,104 --> 01:08:49,474
It's not easy. Really.

1692
01:08:52,014 --> 01:08:55,214
(Trying to set them up nicely at least)

1693
01:08:56,784 --> 01:08:59,354
(Hotel breakfast by Potato is ready.)

1694
01:09:00,384 --> 01:09:01,454
Have breakfast.

1695
01:09:02,124 --> 01:09:03,254
Have breakfast, Kangnam.

1696
01:09:03,784 --> 01:09:05,094
Try the toast.

1697
01:09:06,794 --> 01:09:07,824
It's crazy.

1698
01:09:08,294 --> 01:09:09,464
It's what I wanted.

1699
01:09:09,594 --> 01:09:11,394
I failed the sunny-side ones.

1700
01:09:11,764 --> 01:09:13,094
They're pretty.

1701
01:09:13,494 --> 01:09:15,804
They look good.

1702
01:09:18,034 --> 01:09:19,674
(Biting)

1703
01:09:21,774 --> 01:09:22,973
- Is it good?
- It's so good.

1704
01:09:22,974 --> 01:09:24,004
Really?

1705
01:09:24,744 --> 01:09:25,744
It's so good.

1706
01:09:28,644 --> 01:09:30,544
(Tae Ri wakes up.)

1707
01:09:31,184 --> 01:09:32,484
I made breakfast, Tae Ri.

1708
01:09:33,284 --> 01:09:35,084
It's a buffet.

1709
01:09:36,284 --> 01:09:37,854
- It's a breakfast in a hotel.
- Yes.

1710
01:09:38,824 --> 01:09:40,954
Please try the French toast.

1711
01:09:41,224 --> 01:09:42,624
Thank you.

1712
01:09:44,594 --> 01:09:47,164
(Taking a big bite)

1713
01:09:48,964 --> 01:09:50,034
Is it okay?

1714
01:09:50,764 --> 01:09:51,974
You can sell those.

1715
01:09:52,674 --> 01:09:54,434
- Yes, you can.
- You can sell them.

1716
01:09:56,574 --> 01:09:59,214
(Showing how much she meant it by devouring it)

1717
01:10:00,374 --> 01:10:02,544
I had a hearty meal when I just got up.

1718
01:10:04,114 --> 01:10:05,753
- It was good.
- Okay.

1719
01:10:05,754 --> 01:10:08,054
(A satisfying meal is over.)

1720
01:10:09,324 --> 01:10:11,894
(Meanwhile, at the school in the morning...)

1721
01:10:12,324 --> 01:10:13,454
Are you going to be the pitcher?

1722
01:10:13,854 --> 01:10:15,494
- He hit it.
- Come on.

1723
01:10:16,564 --> 01:10:19,164
(Today's starting pitcher, Cho Ha Yun)

1724
01:10:20,164 --> 01:10:21,903
(Noh Hyo Min, the batter, swings.)

1725
01:10:21,904 --> 01:10:23,134
Hit it. Seriously.

1726
01:10:23,264 --> 01:10:24,604
- It looks good.
- But you...

1727
01:10:24,734 --> 01:10:26,033
(A home run)

1728
01:10:26,034 --> 01:10:27,534
- Seriously?
- You also scolded me, right?

1729
01:10:29,504 --> 01:10:30,574
Come on.

1730
01:10:30,944 --> 01:10:33,944
(He's swallowing the bitterness of defeat by himself.)

1731
01:10:34,374 --> 01:10:37,384
(The lonely pitcher Ha Yun is...)

1732
01:10:37,784 --> 01:10:39,653
Will you introduce yourself?

1733
01:10:39,654 --> 01:10:40,654
(His introduction when we first met him)

1734
01:10:40,754 --> 01:10:41,784
Well...

1735
01:10:43,984 --> 01:10:46,254
(Blinking)

1736
01:10:46,824 --> 01:10:48,923
Should we do this later?

1737
01:10:48,924 --> 01:10:49,993
Yes.

1738
01:10:49,994 --> 01:10:51,564
(He postponed the introduction.)

1739
01:10:52,464 --> 01:10:54,293
(On the first day of the acting class)

1740
01:10:54,294 --> 01:10:56,463
Everyone does an introduction of themselves on the first day.

1741
01:10:56,464 --> 01:10:58,304
Why don't you practice it in advance?

1742
01:10:58,604 --> 01:11:00,833
I'm Cho Ha Yun.

1743
01:11:00,834 --> 01:11:01,903
(He did it this time.)

1744
01:11:01,904 --> 01:11:03,773
How old are you?

1745
01:11:03,774 --> 01:11:06,474
(How old are you?)

1746
01:11:07,644 --> 01:11:10,314
(He's not ready to disclose his age yet.)

1747
01:11:10,614 --> 01:11:12,554
What is Ha Yun like every day?

1748
01:11:13,054 --> 01:11:14,314
He's funny.

1749
01:11:14,854 --> 01:11:15,884
He's a comedian.

1750
01:11:16,624 --> 01:11:18,253
He makes others laugh a lot.

1751
01:11:18,254 --> 01:11:20,453
- That's right.
- He's mischievous.

1752
01:11:20,454 --> 01:11:21,964
Look at my eyes.

1753
01:11:22,064 --> 01:11:25,093
He's kind. He's fun to play with.

1754
01:11:25,094 --> 01:11:26,094
I love that.

1755
01:11:26,534 --> 01:11:29,164
(Why does he become shy in the acting class?)

1756
01:11:29,704 --> 01:11:31,773
(Ha Yun)

1757
01:11:31,774 --> 01:11:33,734
(He's grown up as the gentle youngest son.)

1758
01:11:36,874 --> 01:11:39,044
(He feels the pain half a beat slower.)

1759
01:11:39,744 --> 01:11:42,513
(Ha Yun)

1760
01:11:42,514 --> 01:11:45,184
(He dances half a beat slower.)

1761
01:11:45,954 --> 01:11:47,513
(Cho Ha Yun is a late bloomer.)

1762
01:11:47,514 --> 01:11:48,754
I should have hit it.

1763
01:11:48,854 --> 01:11:50,423
Ha Yun, be careful.

1764
01:11:50,424 --> 01:11:53,423
You can do it, Ha Yun.

1765
01:11:53,424 --> 01:11:55,393
- She said you could do it.
- You can do it.

1766
01:11:55,394 --> 01:11:57,263
(He's getting closer to the class at his own pace.)

1767
01:11:57,264 --> 01:11:58,594
Gosh. It hurts so much.

1768
01:11:59,334 --> 01:12:02,833
It's the seventh class today.

1769
01:12:02,834 --> 01:12:04,673
(7th class)

1770
01:12:04,674 --> 01:12:06,334
We'll go over it quickly.

1771
01:12:06,774 --> 01:12:08,974
We're going to create scenes today.

1772
01:12:09,074 --> 01:12:12,313
We're going to perform the scenes from Tin Man to Lion...

1773
01:12:12,314 --> 01:12:13,874
before Wicked Witch of the West.

1774
01:12:13,944 --> 01:12:17,684
Okay. We're going to sing the chorus part.

1775
01:12:17,784 --> 01:12:19,583
Mr. Choi has prepared...

1776
01:12:19,584 --> 01:12:21,014
- a simple choreography.
- Okay.

1777
01:12:21,484 --> 01:12:22,723
I'll show it to them.

1778
01:12:22,724 --> 01:12:23,924
Yes, show it to them.

1779
01:12:24,254 --> 01:12:25,793
- Do it louder.
- Yes.

1780
01:12:25,794 --> 01:12:27,524
- Sing it louder.
- Should I use my singing voice?

1781
01:12:27,724 --> 01:12:29,793
From the start. Yes, use your singing voice.

1782
01:12:29,794 --> 01:12:30,824
Okay.

1783
01:12:31,864 --> 01:12:34,264
(Starting after clearing his throat)

1784
01:12:35,334 --> 01:12:36,804
Everyone, this was the original move.

1785
01:12:38,734 --> 01:12:40,274
(Excited)

1786
01:12:40,904 --> 01:12:43,244
(Lion helps you by mustering up the courage)

1787
01:12:45,874 --> 01:12:47,444
(Doing his best)

1788
01:12:48,584 --> 01:12:51,314
(Singing the heart of Tin Man from the bottom of his stomach)

1789
01:12:53,514 --> 01:12:54,754
I love it.

1790
01:12:56,884 --> 01:13:00,794
(Ignoring the constraints of the pitch and rhythm)

1791
01:13:03,164 --> 01:13:04,523
(A good friend with a big heart)

1792
01:13:04,524 --> 01:13:05,994
(Every friend with a big heart)

1793
01:13:07,064 --> 01:13:08,064
He's doing it wrong.

1794
01:13:08,065 --> 01:13:09,104
(Crying)

1795
01:13:10,104 --> 01:13:12,874
(Let's go)

1796
01:13:13,434 --> 01:13:15,704
(With Dorothy!)

1797
01:13:16,944 --> 01:13:20,373
Mr. Choi, the kids will mimic that if you do that.

1798
01:13:20,374 --> 01:13:21,414
- Really?
- Yes.

1799
01:13:21,914 --> 01:13:23,813
I think you should sing the original in a brighter way.

1800
01:13:23,814 --> 01:13:24,953
- More brightly?
- Yes.

1801
01:13:24,954 --> 01:13:26,253
- Yes, try smiling.
- Smiling.

1802
01:13:26,254 --> 01:13:27,284
- Be cute.
- Okay.

1803
01:13:27,384 --> 01:13:28,384
Be cute.

1804
01:13:28,854 --> 01:13:31,223
(Got it.)

1805
01:13:31,224 --> 01:13:32,224
Okay.

1806
01:13:32,324 --> 01:13:34,494
- Good.
- Nice!

1807
01:13:35,164 --> 01:13:37,224
- Let's do this.
- Okay.

1808
01:13:37,794 --> 01:13:38,794
Okay.

1809
01:13:39,634 --> 01:13:41,834
(Lion helps you by mustering up the courage)

1810
01:13:42,564 --> 01:13:44,604
(Passing out)

1811
01:13:45,674 --> 01:13:49,544
(They can't help but bow to his talent.)

1812
01:13:50,604 --> 01:13:53,143
- Hold on.
- The pitch is not for me.

1813
01:13:53,144 --> 01:13:54,244
- Is it the pitch?
- Yes.

1814
01:13:54,674 --> 01:13:57,414
(Trying again)

1815
01:13:57,514 --> 01:13:59,053
Let me try it again.

1816
01:13:59,054 --> 01:14:00,114
- Of course.
- Yes.

1817
01:14:02,384 --> 01:14:04,723
(Potato Teacher with perseverance...)

1818
01:14:04,724 --> 01:14:06,224
- Once again? Okay.
- Okay.

1819
01:14:07,794 --> 01:14:12,534
(kept practicing several more times.)

1820
01:14:14,094 --> 01:14:15,833
Do it energetically. Be confident.

1821
01:14:15,834 --> 01:14:16,964
I love the song.

1822
01:14:17,634 --> 01:14:19,004
It can easily become a trot.

1823
01:14:20,134 --> 01:14:22,403
What on earth will happen?

1824
01:14:22,404 --> 01:14:24,044
(Will Potato Teacher's choreography class go on smoothly?)

1825
01:14:24,674 --> 01:14:26,943
(The day of the performance is right around the corner.)

1826
01:14:26,944 --> 01:14:28,383
I'll ask for a heart.

1827
01:14:28,384 --> 01:14:29,514
(Not yet.)

1828
01:14:29,844 --> 01:14:30,844
My home...

1829
01:14:31,554 --> 01:14:34,054
(Is the acting class in trouble?)

1830
01:14:34,554 --> 01:14:36,854
(Refreshing themselves through camping)

1831
01:14:37,254 --> 01:14:39,224
(Eating)

1832
01:14:39,324 --> 01:14:40,424
(It's not a dream, is it?)

1833
01:14:40,524 --> 01:14:41,864
(This is real!)

1834
01:14:42,294 --> 01:14:43,894
(Laughing)

1835
01:14:44,364 --> 01:14:46,333
(Becoming one in the romantic night)

1836
01:14:46,334 --> 01:14:48,133
- Gosh. Eun Soo.
- Is Eun Soo crying?

1837
01:14:48,134 --> 01:14:51,063
(They get to see how they're really feeling.)

1838
01:14:51,064 --> 01:14:53,934
Ms. Kim, I love you.

1839
01:14:54,534 --> 01:14:55,843
(The OST of Curtain Up, Class!)

1840
01:14:55,844 --> 01:14:57,573
("Apple Scent" by Kim Tae Ri, produced by CODE KUNST)

1841
01:14:57,574 --> 01:14:59,414
(Available on all music streaming sites)

1842
01:15:25,813 --> 01:15:27,813
Dramaday.me
